        "caption": "Table 1: Summary of six key properties of our work and the degrees to which they have been addressed in recent papers.",
        "table": "<table id=\"S2.T1.2.1\" class=\"ltx_tabular ltx_align_middle\">\n<tbody class=\"ltx_tbody\">\n<tr id=\"S2.T1.2.1.1.1\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.1.1.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_l ltx_border_r ltx_border_t\" rowspan=\"2\"><span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.1.1.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">Paper</span></td>\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.1.1.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_r ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.1.1.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">Fully</span></td>\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.1.1.3\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_r ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.1.1.3.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">Sporadic</span></td>\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.1.1.4\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_r ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.1.1.4.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">Sporadic</span></td>\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.1.1.5\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_r ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.1.1.5.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">Generalized Data</span></td>\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.1.1.6\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_r ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.1.1.6.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">Loose Graph</span></td>\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.1.1.7\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_r ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.1.1.7.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">Last Iterates</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"S2.T1.2.1.2.2\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.2.2.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_r\"><span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.2.2.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">Decentralized</span></td>\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.2.2.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_r\"><span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.2.2.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">SGDs</span></td>\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.2.2.3\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_r\"><span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.2.2.3.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">Aggregations</span></td>\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.2.2.4\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_r\">\n<span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.2.2.4.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">Heterogeneity </span><span id=\"footnote1\" class=\"ltx_note ltx_role_footnote\"><sup class=\"ltx_note_mark\">1</sup><span class=\"ltx_note_outer\"><span class=\"ltx_note_content\"><sup class=\"ltx_note_mark\">1</sup><span class=\"ltx_tag ltx_tag_note\">1</span>In Assumption <a href=\"#S4.Thmtheorem1\" title=\"Assumption 4.1 (Loss functions). ‣ 4.1 Definitions and Assumptions ‣ 4 Convergence Analysis ‣ Decentralized Sporadic Federated Learning: A Unified Methodology with Generalized Convergence Guarantees\" class=\"ltx_ref\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_ref_tag\">4.1</span></a>-<a href=\"#S4.I2.i3\" title=\"Item (c) ‣ Assumption 4.1 (Loss functions). ‣ 4.1 Definitions and Assumptions ‣ 4 Convergence Analysis ‣ Decentralized Sporadic Federated Learning: A Unified Methodology with Generalized Convergence Guarantees\" class=\"ltx_ref\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_ref_tag\">(c)</span></a>, we consider a more general/milder data heterogeneity assumption based on two parameters <math id=\"footnote1.m1.1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"\\delta\" display=\"inline\"><semantics id=\"footnote1.m1.1b\"><mi id=\"footnote1.m1.1.1\" xref=\"footnote1.m1.1.1.cmml\">δ</mi><annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\" id=\"footnote1.m1.1c\"><ci id=\"footnote1.m1.1.1.cmml\" xref=\"footnote1.m1.1.1\">𝛿</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\" id=\"footnote1.m1.1d\">\\delta</annotation></semantics></math> and <math id=\"footnote1.m2.1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"\\zeta\" display=\"inline\"><semantics id=\"footnote1.m2.1b\"><mi id=\"footnote1.m2.1.1\" xref=\"footnote1.m2.1.1.cmml\">ζ</mi><annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\" id=\"footnote1.m2.1c\"><ci id=\"footnote1.m2.1.1.cmml\" xref=\"footnote1.m2.1.1\">𝜁</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\" id=\"footnote1.m2.1d\">\\zeta</annotation></semantics></math>. This assumption is obtained through <math id=\"footnote1.m3.1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"\\beta\" display=\"inline\"><semantics id=\"footnote1.m3.1b\"><mi id=\"footnote1.m3.1.1\" xref=\"footnote1.m3.1.1.cmml\">β</mi><annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\" id=\"footnote1.m3.1c\"><ci id=\"footnote1.m3.1.1.cmml\" xref=\"footnote1.m3.1.1\">𝛽</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\" id=\"footnote1.m3.1d\">\\beta</annotation></semantics></math>-smoothness rather than restricting the gradient norms to a constant upper bound.</span></span></span>\n</td>\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.2.2.5\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_r\">\n<span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.2.2.5.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">Connectivity </span><span id=\"footnote2\" class=\"ltx_note ltx_role_footnote\"><sup class=\"ltx_note_mark\">2</sup><span class=\"ltx_note_outer\"><span class=\"ltx_note_content\"><sup class=\"ltx_note_mark\">2</sup><span class=\"ltx_tag ltx_tag_note\">2</span>In Assumption <a href=\"#S4.Thmtheorem3\" title=\"Assumption 4.3 (Asymptotic graph connectivity). ‣ 4.1 Definitions and Assumptions ‣ 4 Convergence Analysis ‣ Decentralized Sporadic Federated Learning: A Unified Methodology with Generalized Convergence Guarantees\" class=\"ltx_ref\"><span class=\"ltx_text ltx_ref_tag\">4.3</span></a>, we neither require the underlying network graph to be static, nor <math id=\"footnote2.m1.1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\"><semantics id=\"footnote2.m1.1b\"><mi id=\"footnote2.m1.1.1\" xref=\"footnote2.m1.1.1.cmml\">B</mi><annotation-xml encoding=\"MathML-Content\" id=\"footnote2.m1.1c\"><ci id=\"footnote2.m1.1.1.cmml\" xref=\"footnote2.m1.1.1\">𝐵</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\" id=\"footnote2.m1.1d\">B</annotation></semantics></math>-connected. We instead make a milder assumption that every communication link is expected to be activated infinitely many times as the number of iterations approaches infinity.</span></span></span>\n</td>\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.2.2.6\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_r\"><span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.2.2.6.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">Convergence</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"S2.T1.2.1.3.3\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.3.3.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_l ltx_border_r ltx_border_tt\"><cite class=\"ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_citep\"><span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.3.3.1.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">(</span>Maranjyan et al.<span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.3.3.1.2.2.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">, </span><a href=\"#bib.bib22\" title=\"\" class=\"ltx_ref\">2022</a><span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.3.3.1.3.3\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">)</span></cite></td>\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.3.3.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_border_r ltx_border_tt\"></td>\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.3.3.3\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_r ltx_border_tt\"><span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.3.3.3.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">✓</span></td>\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.3.3.4\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_border_r ltx_border_tt\"></td>\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.3.3.5\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_border_r ltx_border_tt\"></td>\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.3.3.6\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_border_r ltx_border_tt\"></td>\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.3.3.7\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_r ltx_border_tt\"><span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.3.3.7.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">✓</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"S2.T1.2.1.4.4\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n<td id=\"S2.T1.2.1.4.4.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_l ltx_border_r ltx_border_t\"><cite class=\"ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_citep\"><span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.4.4.1.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">(</span>Koloskova et al.<span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.4.4.1.2.2.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">, </span><a href=\"#bib.bib12\" title=\"\" class=\"ltx_ref\">2020</a><span id=\"S2.T1.2.1.4.4.1.3.3\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font